name: ApptBundlePolicy

fields.inlineHelpText: Make this policy available when the dispatcher manually bundles service appointments in the dispatch console. You can have manual bundling and automatic bundling enabled at the same time.
fields.label: Manual Bundling
fields.name: IsManualBundling

fields.inlineHelpText: Make this policy available when automatic bundling is triggered by an automated process. You can have manual bundling and automatic bundling enabled at the same time.
fields.label: Automatic Bundling
fields.name: IsAutomaticBundling

fields.inlineHelpText: Enter the maximum number of bundle members that can be included in a bundle, up to 200.
fields.label: Limit Amount of Bundle Members
fields.name: LimitAmountOfBundleMembers

fields.inlineHelpText: Enter the maximum duration of a bundle, in minutes.
fields.label: Limit Duration of Bundle
fields.name: LimitDurationOfBundle

fields.inlineHelpText: Select the bundle service appointment field used for the bundle’s start time.
fields.label: Bundle Start Time Field Name
fields.name: BundleStartTimeFieldName

fields.inlineHelpText: Select the bundle service appointment field used for the bundle’s end time.
fields.label: Bundle End Time Field Name
fields.name: BundleEndTimeFieldName

fields.inlineHelpText: Subtract the bundle’s start time from the bundle’s end time and compare it to the bundle’s Duration.
fields.label: Time Calculation by Bundle Duration Field
fields.name: IsTimeCalcByBundleDurationFld

fields.inlineHelpText: Use this option only if Time Calculation by Bundle Duration Field is enabled. Enter the bundle’s total time as a constant value, in minutes.
fields.label: Constant Time Value
fields.name: ConstantTimeValue

fields.inlineHelpText: Select the filter criteria used for the bundle members. Only service appointments that meet the criteria can be bundled.
fields.label: Recordset Filter Criteria ID
fields.name: FilterCriteriaId

fields.inlineHelpText: Allow bundling of service appointments with scheduling dependencies.
fields.label: Allow Scheduling Dependencies in Bundle
fields.name: CanAllowSchleDepndInBundle

fields.inlineHelpText: Enter a policy priority number. Must be unique. When the bundle policies are evaluated with automatic bundling, the priority determines the order that the policies are applied.
fields.label: Priority
fields.name: Priority

query: SELECT  Name, CurrencyIsoCode, IsManualBundling, IsAutomaticBundling, LimitAmountOfBundleMembers, LimitDurationOfBundle, BundleStartTimeFieldName, BundleEndTimeFieldName, IsTimeCalcByBundleDurationFld, ConstantTimeValue, FilterCriteriaId, CanAllowSchleDepndInBundle, Priority FROM ApptBundlePolicy
countExternalQuery: SELECT  COUNT(Id), COUNT(Name), COUNT(Priority) FROM ApptBundlePolicy
